{"key":"post-10784500","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10784500</id>\n<content>The fact is, you're casing a species that doesn't require a casing layer and benefits little from one, provided you maintain proper fruiting conditions.&amp;nbsp; It's hard to give advice on something that isn't needed.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The only way a casing helps with cubes is if you're failing to provide a humid environment, and are not misting enough or at the proper times.&amp;nbsp; A casing layer can help in those cases, but with proper care, an uncased bulk substrate will perform as well as a cased one, and soaking/dunking has replaced the casing layer as a way to resupply moisture between flushes.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10791411</next>\n<prev>10784387</prev>\n<first>10782908</first>\n<last>10792084</last>\n<when>1249224630</when>\n<utime>08/02/09 05:50 PM</utime>\n</post>"}